The problem with your code is that you are adding a number (the "fee") to a
a string (account.billing.previous), which will concatenate these two value
values and not perform arithmetic addition as expected. 

You need to convert the strings to numbers before performing the arithmetic
arithmetic operation. So, it should be something like this:

val account = {
  name: "Ada",
  billing: {
    current: "30",
    previous: "12"
   }
};

var charge = parseNumber(account.billing.current);
val fee = 5;
var total = charge + fee;

print(total);
